            "- [ ] View source / comments",
            "- [ ] Test login / credentials",
            "- [ ] File upload testing",
            "- [ ] LFI / RFI testing",
            "- [ ] SQLi testing",
            "",
            "### 🔐 Auth / Credentials",
            "- [ ] Default credentials tested",
            "- [ ] Credential reuse attempted",
            "- [ ] Manual password spray",
            "",
            "### 🧠 Version-Based Attacks",
            "- [ ] searchsploit",
            "- [ ] Manual research (Google)",
            "",
            "--------------------------------------------------",
            "",
            "## 💥 INITIAL ACCESS",
            "",
            "### 🎯 Target Vector",
            "- Service:",
            "- Vulnerability:",
            "- Reason it works:",
            "",
            "### 🚀 Execution",
            "```bash",
            "# exploit command",
            "```",
            "",
            "### 🧾 Proof",
            "- [ ] whoami",
            "- [ ] IP verification",
            "- [ ] Screenshot captured",
            "",
            "### ⚙️ Shell Stabilization",
            "- [ ] python3 pty spawn",
            "- [ ] export TERM=xterm",
            "- [ ] Ctrl+Z → stty raw -echo → fg",
            "",
            "--------------------------------------------------",
            "",
            "## ⬆️ PRIVILEGE ESCALATION",
            "",
            "### 🔍 Enumeration (MANDATORY)",
            "- [ ] linpeas / winpeas",
            "- [ ] sudo -l",
            "- [ ] SUID / SGID binaries",
            "- [ ] Cron jobs",
            "- [ ] Writable directories",
            "- [ ] Running services",
            "- [ ] Credential reuse",
            "",
            "### 🎯 Potential Vectors",
            "| Vector | Reason | Tried | Result |",
            "|--------|--------|------|--------|",
            "|        |        | ⬜ |        |",
            "",
            "### 🚀 Exploitation",
            "```bash",
            "# privilege escalation command",
            "```",
            "",
            "### 🧾 Root Proof",
            "- [ ] proof.txt captured",
            "- [ ] Screenshot captured",
            "",
            "--------------------------------------------------",
            "",
            "## 🧨 STUCK PROTOCOL",
            "",
            "### ⏱️ After 30 Minutes",
            "- [ ] Re-enumerate everything",
            "- [ ] Re-check all ports/services",
            "- [ ] Test credentials across services",
            "- [ ] Try different tools",
            "",
            "### ⏱️ After 60 Minutes",
            "- [ ] Switch to another target",
            "- [ ] Leave clear notes before switching",
            "",
            "--------------------------------------------------",
            "",
            "## 🧹 CLEANUP",
            "- [ ] Remove uploaded exploits",
            "- [ ] Remove shells / binaries",
            "- [ ] Clean temporary files (/tmp)",
            "",
            "--------------------------------------------------",
            "",
            "## 📝 REPORT READY",
            "",
            "### Attack Chain",
            "1. Initial access:",
            "2. Privilege escalation:",
            "",
            "### Evidence Checklist",
            "- [ ] local.txt screenshot",
            "- [ ] proof.txt screenshot",
            "- [ ] whoami proof",
            "",
            "### Mitigation",
            "- Patch:",
            "- Configuration fix:"
          ],
          "guidance": {
            "objective": "Work the exam target methodically while preserving timings, proofs, and a concise attack-chain summary.",
            "checklist": [
              "Confirm all exposed services",
              "Validate initial access path",
              "Document privilege escalation proof"
            ],
            "operator_prompts": [
              "What service deserves manual validation before moving on?",
              "If stuck, what needs re-enumeration first?"
            ],
            "suggested_commands": [
              "nmap -p- --min-rate 1000 <IP>",
              "nmap -sC -sV -oA enum/initial <IP>",
              "searchsploit <service-or-version>"
            ],
            "evidence_prompts": [
              "Capture local.txt and proof.txt proof",
              "Save the key command output used in the successful path"
            ]
          }
